---
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
import Header from "../components/Header.astro";
import Footer from "../components/Footer.astro";
import SnowflakeIcon from "../assets/svg/snowflake.astro";
---

<Layout
  title="About Penqwin | Autonomous Engineering Documentation"
  description="Learn about Penqwin, the platform that uses AI agents to bootstrap your repository documentation and keep it in sync with every code change."
>
  <Header />

  <main class="relative pt-32 pb-24 overflow-hidden">
    <!-- Background Decor -->
    <!-- <div
      class="absolute top-0 left-1/2 -translate-x-1/2 w-full h-full pointer-events-none -z-10"
    >
      <div
        class="absolute top-0 left-1/4 w-[500px] h-[500px] bg-primary/5 blur-[120px] rounded-full opacity-30 animate-pulse-slow"
      >
      </div>
      <div
        class="absolute bottom-1/4 right-1/4 w-[400px] h-[400px] bg-accent/5 blur-[100px] rounded-full opacity-20"
      >
      </div>
    </div> -->

    <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-6">
      <!-- Hero Section -->
      <section class="mb-24">
        <h1
          class="text-5xl md:text-7xl font-serif text-text-primary mb-8 tracking-tight leading-tight"
        >
          About Penqwin
        </h1>
        <div class="space-y-6">
          <p
            class="text-xl md:text-2xl text-text-secondary leading-relaxed font-light"
          >
            Let’s be honest, most developers don’t <span
              class="italic text-primary">hate</span
            > documentation. They just hate writing it after the fact.
          </p>
          <!-- <p class="text-lg text-text-secondary/80 leading-relaxed">
            You build a feature, merge the PR, ship it to production… and then
            someone asks, “Is this documented?” Suddenly you’re staring at a
            blank page trying to explain something you already solved in code.
          </p> -->
        </div>
      </section>

      <!-- Content Sections -->
      <div class="space-y-32">
        <section class="relative">
          <div class="absolute -left-8 top-0 text-primary/20 select-none">
            <span class="text-8xl font-serif">01</span>
          </div>
          <div class="relative pt-4">
            <h2 class="text-3xl font-serif text-text-primary mb-6">
              Documentation that starts with your codebase
            </h2>
            <div class="space-y-4 text-text-secondary leading-relaxed">
              <p>
                Penqwin bootstraps your entire repository documentation in
                minutes. Instead of starting with an empty editor, our agents
                analyze your codebase to build a complete technical suite that
                explains how your system works from the ground up.
              </p>
              <p>
                From there, your team can review, polish, and expand the
                documentation together.
              </p>
              <div class="flex flex-col gap-2 pt-4">
                <!-- <span class="text-white font-medium">No blank pages.</span>
                <span class="text-white font-medium"
                  >No “I’ll write the docs later.”</span
                > -->
                <span class="text-primary font-medium tracking-wide"
                  >The simplest path from code changes to clear documentation.</span
                >
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </section>

        <section class="relative">
          <div class="absolute -left-8 top-0 text-primary/20 select-none">
            <span class="text-8xl font-serif">02</span>
          </div>
          <div class="relative pt-4">
            <h2 class="text-3xl font-serif text-text-primary mb-6">
              Built for the way engineers actually work
            </h2>
            <div class="space-y-4 text-text-secondary leading-relaxed">
              <p>
                Engineering teams move quickly. Documentation often doesn’t keep
                up.
              </p>
              <p>
                Penqwin fits directly into your workflow by using AI agents to
                monitor your repository. When code evolves, the documentation
                evolves with it, surgically updated in real-time so it never
                drifts out of date.
              </p>
              <p>
                The platform combines AI-generated documentation with a clean
                editing environment so teams can refine and maintain docs
                without friction.
              </p>
              <p class="text-text-secondary font-medium italic pt-2">
                Think of it as a starting point for your documentation, not
                another task on your checklist.
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </section>

        <section
          class="bg-bg-secondary/30 border border-border/20 p-8 rounded-3xl backdrop-blur-sm relative overflow-hidden group"
        >
          <div
            class="absolute -right-8 -bottom-8 opacity-[0.03] group-hover:opacity-[0.05] transition-opacity duration-500"
          >
            <SnowflakeIcon class="w-48 h-48" />
          </div>
          <div
            class="space-y-4 text-text-secondary leading-relaxed relative z-10"
          >
            <p class="md:pr-16">
              Penguins survive harsh conditions by staying close together and
              sharing knowledge within the group. Software teams work the same
              way, things run smoother when everyone understands what’s
              happening in the codebase.
            </p>
            <p>Penqwin exists to keep that shared understanding alive.</p>
          </div>
        </section>
      </div>

      <section class="mt-24 text-center">
        <p
          class="text-sm text-text-muted font-medium tracking-[0.2em] uppercase"
        >
          Great software deserves documentation that keeps up with it.
        </p>
      </section>
    </div>
  </main>

  <Footer />
</Layout>
